        <headline>Flood Watch issued August 6 at 2:53PM EDT until August 7 at 12:00AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues to be
possible.

* WHERE...Edgecombe and Halifax counties.

* WHEN...Until midnight EDT tonight.

* IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers,
creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations.
Creeks and streams may rise out of their banks. Flooding may occur
in poor drainage and urban areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- Areas of moderate to locally heavy rainfall are likely to
continue through midnight tonight. Additional rain could
total 1 to 3 inches to as much as 5 inches in spots and
result in additional flash flooding. Low-lying and urban
areas will be the most susceptible to flooding.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood
Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared
to take action should flooding develop.</instruction>
